---
kind: rule
version: "1.0"
name: golden-rule
description: "Reference rule exercising every RuleConfig field."

# Activation — path-glob requires paths to be non-empty
activation: path-glob
paths: ["src/**/*.go", "internal/**/*.go"]
always-apply: false

# Copilot-specific agent exclusion
exclude-agents: [code-review]

# Multi-target overrides
targets:
  claude:
    suppress-fidelity-warnings: false
    skip-synthesis: false
    instructions-override: ""
    provider:
      custom-key: "claude-rule-value"
  antigravity:
    suppress-fidelity-warnings: true
---
# Golden Rule

This body becomes the rule's instructions at compile time.

Always write tests before implementation. Use table-driven tests in Go.
